WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:17.330 --> 00:00:20.540
Did you know there's an awesome treasure at the end of this sea?!

3
00:00:20.540 --> 00:00:23.340
And whoever gets it becomes King of the Pirates!

4
00:00:23.340 --> 00:00:24.960
Isn't that exciting?!

5
00:00:24.960 --> 00:00:28.010
Cool new adventures are waiting out there!

6
00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:38.060
BON VOYAGE! Light the ember of courage and let the fire grow

7
00:00:38.060 --> 00:00:45.660
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

8
00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:48.210
Back when we first started

9
00:00:48.210 --> 00:00:53.430
we had separate ideas about where we would soon go

10
00:00:53.740 --> 00:00:55.380
Things have changed now,

11
00:00:55.380 --> 00:01:00.440
when we look towards our dreams we all share one telescope

12
00:01:00.730 --> 00:01:05.680
When you find that your heart's been led astray

13
00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:09.980
time to calibrate your compasses

14
00:01:09.980 --> 00:01:13.010
Set a new course, turn the tables now

15
00:01:13.010 --> 00:01:20.300
BON VOYAGE! Shed your previous baggage, forget the past

16
00:01:20.300 --> 00:01:27.140
Smiles can weather a storm, we know that better than anyone

17
00:01:27.140 --> 00:01:29.080
Don't you fret,

18
00:01:29.080 --> 00:01:34.900
tears shed along the way to your dreams are not in vain

19
00:01:34.900 --> 00:01:41.100
You know that you're all PRECIOUS IN MY LIFE

20
00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:49.210
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

21
00:01:50.090 --> 00:01:54.470
<b>Love Song</b>

22
00:01:51.800 --> 00:01:53.180
Luffy...

23
00:01:53.180 --> 00:01:57.350
Enel most likely has
that golden bell by now.

24
00:02:00.730 --> 00:02:03.770
Then I'll just have to take it back!

25
00:02:03.770 --> 00:02:05.060
I'm borrowing this!

26
00:02:19.830 --> 00:02:24.500
Even Heaven's Gate... was blown
away in the blink of an eye.

27
00:02:24.920 --> 00:02:27.420
I can't believe Angel Island is gone...

28
00:02:27.420 --> 00:02:30.050
What're we supposed to do now?

29
00:02:30.050 --> 00:02:33.800
For now, let's head to Cloud End
and escape to the Blue Sea.

30
00:02:33.800 --> 00:02:35.050
We have no other choice!

31
00:02:35.050 --> 00:02:39.220
But there are still so many people
in the White-White Sea!

32
00:02:39.760 --> 00:02:41.560
What are we supposed to do?!

33
00:02:41.560 --> 00:02:45.770
The milky roads are gone, so how do we
get those ships down to the White Sea?!

34
00:02:45.770 --> 00:02:48.190
So we're just giving up on them?!

35
00:03:03.160 --> 00:03:06.330
It won't be long before
this place is blown up too!

36
00:03:09.630 --> 00:03:12.130
The White-White Sea is...

37
00:03:15.050 --> 00:03:18.720
Skypiea is fading away...

38
00:03:34.900 --> 00:03:36.900
So this is it...

39
00:03:38.780 --> 00:03:40.160
Magnificent!

40
00:03:41.870 --> 00:03:47.370
The glorious bell, pride of
the legendary city of Shandora!

41
00:03:47.370 --> 00:03:49.880
Amazing!

42
00:03:49.880 --> 00:03:53.340
How fitting that I, God,
should possess such a wonder!

43
00:03:53.340 --> 00:03:58.550
The bell that proclaimed the start of
this land's 400-year-old conflict...

44
00:03:59.090 --> 00:04:02.430
Heads up! Something else is falling!

45
00:04:02.430 --> 00:04:03.010
What now...?

46
00:04:03.350 --> 00:04:04.930
Hit the deck!

47
00:04:09.020 --> 00:04:09.940
A leaf...

48
00:04:15.690 --> 00:04:16.690
Oh?

49
00:04:17.200 --> 00:04:19.030
There's something written on it...

50
00:04:19.950 --> 00:04:20.910
A message!

51
00:04:21.320 --> 00:04:23.030
It's from Luffy and Nami!

52
00:04:24.450 --> 00:04:25.870
What does it say?!

53
00:04:26.790 --> 00:04:30.830
"Chop down this huge vine
so it falls toward the west."

54
00:04:30.830 --> 00:04:33.800
What?!

55
00:04:33.800 --> 00:04:37.510
And... what would be
the point of doing that?

56
00:04:51.770 --> 00:04:55.570
I've accomplished all
that I set out to do.

57
00:04:55.570 --> 00:04:57.190
All that remains...

58
00:05:00.450 --> 00:05:04.330
is to destroy this land and the
cumuloimperator clouds with my Raigo

59
00:05:04.330 --> 00:05:07.200
and set off for the Endless Vearth.

60
00:05:10.580 --> 00:05:14.340
Now that the time has come,
I almost hate to go.

61
00:05:18.630 --> 00:05:19.550
Enel!

62
00:05:20.550 --> 00:05:22.220
That fiend!

63
00:05:23.220 --> 00:05:26.930
Is it just me, or is this one
bigger than before...?

64
00:05:27.890 --> 00:05:30.810
We... can kiss our escape goodbye...

65
00:05:32.060 --> 00:05:34.520
We're stuck here!

66
00:05:41.150 --> 00:05:43.320
Farewell, Skypiea.

67
00:05:46.280 --> 00:05:49.700
It's even bigger than
last time! That bastard!

68
00:05:49.700 --> 00:05:51.120
True.

69
00:05:51.120 --> 00:05:53.120
Now that he's got the golden bell,

70
00:05:53.120 --> 00:05:55.540
he no longer has any
business with this land.

71
00:05:56.880 --> 00:05:58.840
Nami, weren't you going to escape?

72
00:06:01.840 --> 00:06:03.840
You expect me to leave now?

73
00:06:03.840 --> 00:06:06.050
You want to ring that
golden bell, right?

74
00:06:06.550 --> 00:06:08.970
Yeah! I'm gonna ring it!

75
00:06:09.970 --> 00:06:13.600
Oh, please, you can't
even control the waver.

76
00:06:13.600 --> 00:06:18.570
You'll just keep jumping anyway if I leave,
so let me shoot you up there instead.

77
00:06:21.150 --> 00:06:21.990
In return...

78
00:06:24.280 --> 00:06:27.490
promise me I'll survive!

79
00:06:28.370 --> 00:06:30.410
Yeah, alright! Thanks!

80
00:06:31.370 --> 00:06:33.920
Everyone's still down there!

81
00:06:33.920 --> 00:06:37.130
We've only got one shot at this!

82
00:06:38.500 --> 00:06:42.630
Please tell me you all received
my message down there...

83
00:06:44.340 --> 00:06:48.390
They're gonna jump to the ship by
ramping off the vine as it falls?!

84
00:06:48.890 --> 00:06:50.600
What else could it mean?

85
00:06:51.220 --> 00:06:53.390
That's crazy...

86
00:06:53.390 --> 00:06:55.850
Feel free to go up and stop him.

87
00:06:55.850 --> 00:06:57.230
He won't stop and you know it!

88
00:06:59.270 --> 00:07:03.240
Regardless of how reckless it is,
we have to let him try!

89
00:07:05.530 --> 00:07:07.280
Wh-What the...?!

90
00:07:07.280 --> 00:07:08.490
Long Nose!

91
00:07:08.490 --> 00:07:09.830
Yeah, I got him!

92
00:07:11.410 --> 00:07:13.660
We'll fall to the ruins at this rate!

93
00:07:13.660 --> 00:07:15.370
Keep away from the vine for now!

94
00:07:15.370 --> 00:07:16.580
Escape to solid ground!

95
00:07:19.500 --> 00:07:20.750
This one's up to me!

96
00:07:20.750 --> 00:07:22.630
Cut it toward the ship, right?!

97
00:07:22.630 --> 00:07:23.710
What?! But...!

98
00:07:24.220 --> 00:07:29.800
The only ones on this sky island who can
reach Enel before that thing is dropped...

99
00:07:29.800 --> 00:07:30.470
Hey, Zoro!

100
00:07:30.850 --> 00:07:32.970
...are those two!

101
00:07:38.350 --> 00:07:40.940
Neither fight nor flight
will serve you now.

102
00:07:41.860 --> 00:07:43.990
Is it still that difficult to grasp?

103
00:07:43.990 --> 00:07:49.910
Your fate was sealed the moment you
became part of the survival game.

104
00:07:52.660 --> 00:07:55.120
I-I-Is he okay?!

105
00:07:55.120 --> 00:07:56.410
We're counting on you!

106
00:07:56.410 --> 00:08:01.040
You're the only one who
can cut that thing down!

107
00:08:03.960 --> 00:08:07.050
Quit making all these holes, dammit!

108
00:08:18.890 --> 00:08:20.690
Alright! He cut it!

109
00:08:24.480 --> 00:08:25.650
Zoro!

110
00:08:34.240 --> 00:08:36.250
Trifling insects!

111
00:08:41.210 --> 00:08:43.090
You bastard!

112
00:08:43.090 --> 00:08:46.420
B-B-But he did it! He cut it!

113
00:08:46.920 --> 00:08:48.590
Oh no...

114
00:08:48.590 --> 00:08:49.260
Look!

115
00:08:52.180 --> 00:08:53.800
It's not coming down...

116
00:08:54.560 --> 00:08:55.810
He cut it, though!

117
00:08:56.430 --> 00:08:59.140
What a tough vine!

118
00:08:59.140 --> 00:09:01.600
Can we even be sure it's a real plant?!

119
00:09:01.600 --> 00:09:04.110
How pathetic...

120
00:09:04.110 --> 00:09:06.570
As if meddling outsiders
have what it takes...

121
00:09:06.940 --> 00:09:08.860
Wyper, don't do it!

122
00:09:08.860 --> 00:09:10.150
Quiet!

123
00:09:10.650 --> 00:09:15.280
We inherited Kalgara's wishes, so it's vital
that we be the ones to ring that bell!

124
00:09:15.280 --> 00:09:18.660
Straw Hat never had
anything to do with this!

125
00:09:18.660 --> 00:09:20.160
Leave him be, Robin!

126
00:09:20.160 --> 00:09:25.210
He's too injured to get in our way!
We have to focus on knocking over that vine!

127
00:09:25.210 --> 00:09:26.550
Luffy and Nami depend on it!

128
00:09:27.550 --> 00:09:31.340
So far, Zoro's cut half of the stem...

129
00:09:31.340 --> 00:09:34.140
The whole thing should be
tilting by now.

130
00:09:34.140 --> 00:09:37.470
When I attack it with my
Dance of Exploding Stars...

131
00:09:38.970 --> 00:09:42.940
it'll collapse with a chilling scream!

132
00:09:43.940 --> 00:09:48.440
As usual, it has fallen to me to push
our pirate crew across the finish line!

133
00:09:48.440 --> 00:09:53.410
Robin, see to our fallen allies!

134
00:09:54.280 --> 00:09:56.240
They look like a kashiwa-mochi cake.

135
00:09:56.240 --> 00:09:57.660
Full speed ahead!

136
00:10:05.040 --> 00:10:10.970
Four hundred years ago, an explorer
told a lie that he saw a city of gold.

137
00:10:12.590 --> 00:10:16.800
Although he became the object of ridicule,
his descendants believed his words...

138
00:10:17.390 --> 00:10:21.310
and continue to search for
the City of Gold in the Blue Sea.

139
00:10:31.820 --> 00:10:33.820
If we ring the golden bell,

140
00:10:33.820 --> 00:10:37.030
we can let them know
the City of Gold is in the sky.

141
00:10:38.080 --> 00:10:41.250
That's what that
straw hat boy is thinking.

142
00:10:41.250 --> 00:10:42.910
Exploding Star!

143
00:10:43.620 --> 00:10:45.420
What better reason could there be?

144
00:10:46.380 --> 00:10:48.090
That's romance.

145
00:10:49.040 --> 00:10:50.880
Even in a situation like this...

146
00:10:51.920 --> 00:10:54.550
going so far as to lose
his chance to escape...

147
00:10:56.050 --> 00:10:57.470
It borders on absurd!

148
00:10:57.470 --> 00:10:58.470
Lethal Exploding Star!

149
00:10:58.470 --> 00:10:59.470
Exploding Star Star!

150
00:10:59.470 --> 00:11:00.890
Usopp's Rubber Band of Doom!

151
00:11:00.890 --> 00:11:02.270
Rolling Exploding Star!

152
00:11:02.270 --> 00:11:03.390
Exploding Star!

153
00:11:11.480 --> 00:11:12.940
Tell me...

154
00:11:13.610 --> 00:11:16.200
the name of this
explorer's descendant...

155
00:11:16.780 --> 00:11:19.280
Mont Blanc Cricket...

156
00:11:21.120 --> 00:11:24.000
Then his ancestor from
400 years ago...

157
00:11:26.620 --> 00:11:28.630
Would his name be...

158
00:11:28.630 --> 00:11:30.590
Noland?

159
00:11:31.130 --> 00:11:32.130
What?

160
00:11:33.590 --> 00:11:34.470
Wyper?

161
00:11:35.720 --> 00:11:38.220
What's going on, Wyper?!

162
00:11:40.720 --> 00:11:43.720
Is this a miracle...

163
00:11:45.020 --> 00:11:47.940
Great Warrior Kalgara?!

164
00:11:51.980 --> 00:11:53.030
Come on, Nola!

165
00:11:53.030 --> 00:11:56.900
We'll ring the bell again today so that
the sound reaches to the end of the sky!

166
00:11:56.900 --> 00:12:01.620
This sound you love so much...
Let's send it to Noland!

167
00:12:28.350 --> 00:12:29.020
What the...?!

168
00:12:37.030 --> 00:12:38.900
What was that?

169
00:12:39.780 --> 00:12:43.330
But it's crazy that shock didn't
move the vine at all...

170
00:12:43.330 --> 00:12:45.410
Well, this time it'll be Triple Explo–

171
00:12:45.410 --> 00:12:46.080
Stand back.

172
00:13:01.300 --> 00:13:03.050
Reject!

173
00:13:11.690 --> 00:13:12.810
Are you kidding me?!

174
00:13:12.810 --> 00:13:13.770
Wyper!

175
00:13:16.030 --> 00:13:16.900
How foolish...!

176
00:13:16.900 --> 00:13:19.320
He used a reject dial...

177
00:13:20.240 --> 00:13:24.200
Snap in two, Giant Jack!

178
00:13:32.960 --> 00:13:37.590
It's coming down!

179
00:13:40.220 --> 00:13:42.220
Here goes! Get on, Luffy!

180
00:13:43.220 --> 00:13:44.550
Give it all you can!

181
00:13:46.890 --> 00:13:47.890
To be honest...

182
00:13:48.680 --> 00:13:54.690
this will be the first time I've run
this jet dial at max power...

183
00:13:55.060 --> 00:13:59.190
I won't be able to control
something this powerful!

184
00:13:59.190 --> 00:14:00.280
That's fine by me!

185
00:14:00.650 --> 00:14:01.450
Okay!

186
00:14:05.320 --> 00:14:06.620
Here we go, Luffy!

187
00:14:06.620 --> 00:14:07.370
Yeah!

188
00:14:14.920 --> 00:14:16.340
It's coming down!

189
00:14:17.000 --> 00:14:18.130
Look!

190
00:14:18.130 --> 00:14:20.710
What in the world is going on?!

191
00:14:21.170 --> 00:14:24.430
Luffy! Nami! We're all
counting on you!

192
00:14:24.430 --> 00:14:29.350
If the sky island disappears now,
we won't be able to ring the golden bell!

193
00:14:29.720 --> 00:14:31.230
You'll ring it, right?!

194
00:14:31.230 --> 00:14:34.310
You'll let Mr. Cricket hear it, right?!

195
00:14:36.020 --> 00:14:38.730
You better make that
jump to Enel's ship!

196
00:14:39.610 --> 00:14:41.110
Go!

197
00:14:41.110 --> 00:14:43.990
Everything depends on you two!

198
00:14:43.990 --> 00:14:45.070
Go!

199
00:14:54.370 --> 00:14:56.170
My, my...

200
00:14:56.170 --> 00:15:00.300
Why can't you sit still
and wait for my Raigo to finish?

201
00:15:00.880 --> 00:15:03.670
How impudently impatient...

202
00:15:05.630 --> 00:15:07.220
I have no choice, then.

203
00:15:15.890 --> 00:15:19.400
It's sheer insolence to
try and reach me!

204
00:15:19.400 --> 00:15:22.480
You need to be taught a lesson!

205
00:15:22.940 --> 00:15:24.740
Mamaragan!

206
00:15:34.540 --> 00:15:36.170
That bastard...!

207
00:15:36.170 --> 00:15:38.750
He's trying to sink the vine
by taking out its base!

208
00:15:41.210 --> 00:15:42.550
Do something, Nami!

209
00:15:42.550 --> 00:15:44.050
What am I supposed to do?!

210
00:15:44.050 --> 00:15:45.840
We're already climbing up!

211
00:15:46.220 --> 00:15:49.850
We won't get high enough if he
removes the vine's foundation!

212
00:15:50.260 --> 00:15:52.260
We'll fall just short of Enel!

213
00:15:55.100 --> 00:15:57.140
Upper Yard is getting bombarded!

214
00:16:08.070 --> 00:16:10.490
I don't care if you're
immune to lightning!

215
00:16:10.490 --> 00:16:13.160
It won't matter one iota
if you can't make it here!

216
00:16:13.910 --> 00:16:19.040
Plummet far below and await
Raigo's completion, rubber man!

217
00:16:29.010 --> 00:16:31.890
Upper Yard is... being pulverized.

218
00:16:35.100 --> 00:16:37.020
Luffy!

219
00:16:37.020 --> 00:16:38.140
Nami!

220
00:16:41.770 --> 00:16:46.690
He's really intent on keeping
his distance from you, huh?

221
00:16:46.690 --> 00:16:49.320
Let him try!

222
00:16:51.700 --> 00:16:54.240
It's exposing the ruins!

223
00:16:58.160 --> 00:17:01.540
These attacks will
tear up the foundation.

224
00:17:01.880 --> 00:17:04.710
Wyper ended up on
the ground down there!

225
00:17:04.710 --> 00:17:06.000
Zoro, too!

226
00:17:06.880 --> 00:17:09.510
That son of a bitch!

227
00:17:13.550 --> 00:17:15.310
The ruins...

228
00:17:19.600 --> 00:17:21.810
It's useless, Enel.

229
00:17:24.570 --> 00:17:27.780
You can't erase...

230
00:17:27.780 --> 00:17:29.240
W-Wyper!

231
00:17:29.990 --> 00:17:35.450
...the history of the proud warriors
who lived in Shandora!

232
00:17:40.460 --> 00:17:47.250
Be it here or anywhere else, its grand
power can create and nurture...

233
00:17:47.250 --> 00:17:49.920
Bringing it down isn't so easy a task!

234
00:17:50.550 --> 00:17:54.930
No matter how many forests
you burn to ash...

235
00:17:55.470 --> 00:17:59.640
No matter how many ruins
you lay to waste...

236
00:18:03.650 --> 00:18:05.400
This land will persevere!

237
00:18:16.910 --> 00:18:18.450
Get out of there, Wyper!

238
00:18:17.580 --> 00:18:18.450
It's dangerous!

239
00:18:18.450 --> 00:18:20.330
Wyper's gonna die!

240
00:18:20.330 --> 00:18:22.040
Let me go, stupid!

241
00:18:22.410 --> 00:18:23.170
Huh?

242
00:18:23.170 --> 00:18:26.500
The drivel from below won't let up.

243
00:19:04.580 --> 00:19:07.210
Wouldn't the vearth...? That's right!

244
00:19:17.010 --> 00:19:18.510
It's not sinking!

245
00:19:19.390 --> 00:19:22.720
Upper Yard held together!

246
00:19:26.060 --> 00:19:28.150
What great power!

247
00:19:32.570 --> 00:19:34.280
That's right...!

248
00:19:34.280 --> 00:19:37.280
Vearth is utterly magnificent!

249
00:19:40.780 --> 00:19:45.040
Vearth was never something
to have fought over,

250
00:19:45.040 --> 00:19:50.420
and yet so much blood has been
spilled and so many lives lost...

251
00:19:51.040 --> 00:19:55.300
How could we be so blind
for these past 400 years?!

252
00:19:58.340 --> 00:19:59.890
Wyper!

253
00:20:04.430 --> 00:20:06.940
Wyper!

254
00:20:08.770 --> 00:20:10.900
Move it! The vine is falling!

255
00:20:10.900 --> 00:20:12.360
Get over here, now!

256
00:20:13.110 --> 00:20:14.820
Go...

257
00:20:20.490 --> 00:20:25.200
Go, Straw Hat!

258
00:20:28.040 --> 00:20:31.630
Here I come, Enel!

259
00:20:32.380 --> 00:20:34.630
The impudence of
every last one of them...

260
00:20:34.630 --> 00:20:39.340
Give back that golden bell!

261
00:20:39.340 --> 00:20:41.600
Enough already!

262
00:20:41.600 --> 00:20:42.890
I'm sick of you!

263
00:20:42.890 --> 00:20:45.350
It's grown large enough...

264
00:20:47.640 --> 00:20:49.480
Disappear with the land!

265
00:20:53.860 --> 00:20:55.610
Raigo!

266
00:21:14.250 --> 00:21:15.960
Thanks, Nami!

267
00:21:15.960 --> 00:21:16.880
What?!

268
00:21:17.380 --> 00:21:19.260
I won't let your help go to waste!

269
00:21:21.220 --> 00:21:23.090
Wait, Luffy!

270
00:21:24.850 --> 00:21:26.560
The ship is the other way!

271
00:21:32.480 --> 00:21:36.530
Luffy! That thing is a vortex
of air and lightning!

272
00:21:36.530 --> 00:21:38.610
Who knows what'll happen to you?!

273
00:21:39.240 --> 00:21:45.580
What can you do before this
tremendous power, rubber man?!

274
00:22:12.690 --> 00:22:17.940
Gum-Gum...

275
00:22:17.940 --> 00:22:25.320
Fi

276
00:22:19.650 --> 00:22:25.320
re

277
00:22:21.950 --> 00:22:25.320
works!

278
00:22:25.320 --> 00:22:27.450
Golden Peony!

279
00:22:39.880 --> 00:22:47.140
The sky island weather was so nice before you
messed it up with your stupid thunder!

280
00:22:47.140 --> 00:22:49.060
You lightning freak!

281
00:22:52.270 --> 00:22:55.150
Wh-What's happening to
the electric discharge?!

282
00:22:56.810 --> 00:22:58.610
That's right...!

283
00:22:59.110 --> 00:23:03.570
That gold on his hand is
the perfect conductor for electricity!

284
00:23:05.160 --> 00:23:09.620
Very well! I'll drop it before
all the electricity discharges!

285
00:23:11.410 --> 00:23:13.580
Begone!

286
00:23:17.460 --> 00:23:18.790
Captain McKinley!

287
00:23:19.130 --> 00:23:20.420
Please stop.

288
00:23:20.420 --> 00:23:21.500
This is God Land.

289
00:23:22.260 --> 00:23:23.380
There's no point!

290
00:23:23.380 --> 00:23:25.260
I don't care if there's no point!

291
00:23:25.260 --> 00:23:30.510
What else are people to do when
faced with a life or death situation?

292
00:23:31.180 --> 00:23:34.810
In order to survive,
we chose to abandon our land.

293
00:23:34.810 --> 00:23:39.310
We can't go back and we
can't move forward...

294
00:23:40.070 --> 00:23:44.110
All that we can do is pray.

295
00:23:44.900 --> 00:23:54.330
When we hear the "song of
the island," this battle will end.

296
00:23:57.080 --> 00:24:01.460
Will there even be any
survivors at this point...?

297
00:24:02.210 --> 00:24:06.260
Had I the courage to stand up
to Enel, I wonder...

298
00:24:07.090 --> 00:24:10.140
would I have had
to involve them...?

299
00:24:11.260 --> 00:24:13.060
Say, Suu...

300
00:24:15.430 --> 00:24:18.060
I wonder if there really is a god...

301
00:24:18.560 --> 00:24:22.020
If there is, I wonder if he'd save us...

302
00:24:25.240 --> 00:24:28.320
Please... if you really exist...

303
00:24:29.570 --> 00:24:32.700
please protect them, God!

304
00:24:33.410 --> 00:24:35.700
Please... make a miracle happen!

305
00:24:36.620 --> 00:24:39.830
Please, God, protect this land!

306
00:24:51.760 --> 00:24:54.970
Clear up!

307
00:25:12.490 --> 00:25:14.990
The mass of thunderclouds is gone!

308
00:25:16.410 --> 00:25:18.580
What happened?

309
00:25:21.420 --> 00:25:22.290
What?!

310
00:25:37.520 --> 00:25:39.310
Right on, Luffy!

311
00:25:49.940 --> 00:25:52.320
Ring it, Straw Hat!

312
00:25:52.320 --> 00:25:55.370
Shine the Light of Shandora!

313
00:25:55.370 --> 00:25:57.490
Go, Luffy!

314
00:25:57.490 --> 00:26:01.750
Let us hear the song of the island!

315
00:26:03.120 --> 00:26:08.170
How dare you destroy my Raigo,
you damn Blue Sea monkey?!

316
00:26:08.170 --> 00:26:11.510
How about I ring you too?!

317
00:26:11.510 --> 00:26:14.090
You insolent wretch!

318
00:26:17.060 --> 00:26:19.270
200 Million...

319
00:26:19.930 --> 00:26:21.940
Volts:

320
00:26:22.390 --> 00:26:24.940
Amaru!

321
00:26:27.400 --> 00:26:28.730
What the hell is that?!

322
00:26:28.730 --> 00:26:30.650
"Ring," you say?!

323
00:26:30.650 --> 00:26:32.950
Ring the golden bell?!

324
00:26:32.950 --> 00:26:37.530
Its next ringing will signal
the end of this battle!

325
00:26:37.530 --> 00:26:41.750
What good will it do to cling
to obsolete legends?!

326
00:26:41.750 --> 00:26:43.790
I am God!

327
00:26:49.550 --> 00:26:54.470
You are but a lone paramecia type!

328
00:26:54.470 --> 00:27:01.980
My logia powers guarantee
my ability to utterly crush you!

329
00:27:04.100 --> 00:27:06.810
I already told you
that won't work on me!

330
00:27:08.020 --> 00:27:10.320
"God" this! "God" that! Shut up!

331
00:27:10.730 --> 00:27:14.780
What kind of god
refuses to save anything?!

332
00:27:25.580 --> 00:27:26.710
Oh?

333
00:27:26.710 --> 00:27:29.840
You grabbed hold of it
to avoid being skewered, huh?

334
00:27:29.840 --> 00:27:31.170
Luffy!

335
00:27:33.880 --> 00:27:37.260
What's your next move, rubber man?!
There's nowhere to escape to!

336
00:27:38.180 --> 00:27:43.220
As your arm pulls more taut,
the spear will pierce you even deeper!

337
00:27:43.220 --> 00:27:46.390
And squirming out of this
will cause you to fall!

338
00:27:48.610 --> 00:27:52.030
I must commend you
for climbing this high!

339
00:27:52.030 --> 00:27:56.450
However, this is as far as you go,
and this land is finished too!

340
00:27:56.910 --> 00:27:58.870
I'll create as many Raigos as it takes!

341
00:28:02.950 --> 00:28:05.710
This is our duty as citizens.

342
00:28:06.920 --> 00:28:08.330
I'm sorry!

343
00:28:12.420 --> 00:28:13.500
Luffy...

344
00:28:14.420 --> 00:28:17.300
Is the sky island...
going to disappear?!

345
00:28:24.470 --> 00:28:26.770
So you chose to fall!

346
00:28:33.440 --> 00:28:34.230
Luffy!

347
00:28:36.190 --> 00:28:38.070
Nami! Out of the way!

348
00:28:43.490 --> 00:28:44.790
Wh-What're you...?!

349
00:28:45.250 --> 00:28:48.080
Don't mess with me, earlobes!

350
00:28:48.080 --> 00:28:52.540
Gum-Gum Rocket!

351
00:28:55.000 --> 00:28:57.920
Gum-Gum...

352
00:28:58.880 --> 00:29:01.300
Another attempt?!

353
00:29:01.800 --> 00:29:04.010
Until the bell rings!

354
00:29:04.470 --> 00:29:06.640
You'll be skewered
for certain this time!

355
00:29:06.640 --> 00:29:09.730
...Golden Rifle!

356
00:29:13.730 --> 00:29:14.480
Too fast!

357
00:29:32.080 --> 00:29:35.420
When you return to Jaya...

358
00:29:36.300 --> 00:29:39.130
what will you think
when you see we've gone?

359
00:29:40.760 --> 00:29:44.140
Hold on a little longer!
I'll send a message that...

360
00:29:45.760 --> 00:29:48.220
we are here!

361
00:29:53.860 --> 00:29:57.190
Shine the Light of Shandora!

362
00:30:00.490 --> 00:30:04.910
It's been 400 years since
the battle in the sky started.

363
00:30:05.240 --> 00:30:09.370
Just once, we wanted to...

364
00:30:10.620 --> 00:30:13.370
That's right. The sacred ground will...

365
00:30:16.790 --> 00:30:19.840
sing again...

366
00:30:25.260 --> 00:30:27.930
someday, for sure.

367
00:30:39.940 --> 00:30:45.990
Six years ago, I saw a giant city of gold
on the Grand Line island of Jaya!

368
00:30:50.370 --> 00:30:53.540
The City of Gold exists! I swear it!

369
00:31:00.590 --> 00:31:08.850
No one has ever disproved the existence
of the City of Gold or the sky island.

370
00:31:09.260 --> 00:31:12.020
That's what romance is!

371
00:31:12.020 --> 00:31:16.650
Now reach!

372
00:31:16.650 --> 00:31:17.480
Chestnut head!

373
00:31:18.150 --> 00:31:19.400
Can you hear it?

374
00:31:20.650 --> 00:31:22.740
The City of Gold is here!

375
00:31:23.780 --> 00:31:26.110
For 400 years...

376
00:31:26.910 --> 00:31:28.620
the City of Gold has been here...

377
00:31:32.200 --> 00:31:37.880
in the sky!

378
00:31:44.360 --> 00:31:49.880
When you're lost and alone, call out and lead me to your side

379
00:31:50.100 --> 00:31:55.300
As you wander far from home, you search the sky and never hide

380
00:31:55.300 --> 00:31:58.100
You are so much like the moon

381
00:31:58.100 --> 00:32:02.750
Calmer than a star, your twinkling's lost

382
00:32:06.200 --> 00:32:15.150
A deep reflection shines, you slowly leave, fading, and what's the cost?

383
00:32:15.210 --> 00:32:20.380
Stay as you are, don't lose your way

384
00:32:20.380 --> 00:32:28.690
Let my words guide you, and look ahead until the day!

385
00:32:29.330 --> 00:32:35.580
Don't give up on your dreams, through endless nights they come to you

386
00:32:35.580 --> 00:32:41.200
If you stop, you'll never see them shining through!

387
00:32:42.440 --> 00:32:46.970
Will you return? Maybe not... Will you learn? I hope you do

388
00:32:46.970 --> 00:32:53.360
Please put your past to rest, and live your life anew.
